<DOC><DOCNO> AP891006-0270 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-10-06-89 2040EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r f AM-Vitro-Anchor     10-06 0128</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Vitro-Anchor,0134</SECOND><HEAD>Mexican Glass Maker Extends Bid</HEAD><DATELINE>TAMPA, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Vitro, S.A. announced Friday that it againwas extending its tender offer for Tampa's Anchor Glass ContainerCorp., this time until Oct. 13.   The Mexican glassmaker said so far 8,944,976 shares of Anchor'scommon stock have been tendered to THR Corp., a subsidary of Vitro.These shares, plus 1,430,300 shares owned by THR and itsaffiliates, represent about 75 percent of Anchor's outstandingcommon shares.   Vitro said it has entered into a confidentiality agreement withAnchor under which the Tampa glassmaker has agreed to provide Vitrothe same confidential information provided to third parties.   Vitro made an unsolicited $20-a-share offer for Anchor Aug. 9and several times has extended its offer a week at a time.</TEXT></DOC>